Class Internship

java.lang.Object
team5.Internship
public class Internship extends Object
Represents an internship opportunity in the system. This class encapsulates all details about an internship posting including title, description, level, preferred major, application dates, status, company information, and available slots. Internships must be approved by Career Center Staff before becoming visible to eligible students.

  • Constructor Details

    • Internship

      public Internship(String internshipId, String title, String description, InternshipLevel internshipLevel, StudentMajor preferredMajor, LocalDate applicationOpenDate, LocalDate applicationCloseDate, InternshipStatus status, String companyName, String companyRep, int numOfSlots)
      Constructs a new Internship with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      internshipId - the unique identifier for the internship
      title - the title of the internship position
      description - a detailed description of the internship
      internshipLevel - the difficulty level (BASIC, INTERMEDIATE, or ADVANCED)
      preferredMajor - the preferred major for applicants
      applicationOpenDate - the date when applications open
      applicationCloseDate - the date when applications close
      status - the approval status (PENDING, APPROVED, REJECTED, or FILLED)
      companyName - the name of the company offering the internship
      companyRep - the ID/email of the company representative managing this internship
      numOfSlots - the number of available positions (maximum 10)
